Rovato, Italy – There are no fans lining the road.
Professional cyclist Davide Martinelli has achieved a moral victory, though, by using his bike to help deliver medicine to elderly residents and others in need during the coronavirus pandemic.
In this image taken on Tuesday, April 14, 2020, Italian professional cyclist Davide Martinelli, checks his smartphone to deliver medicine to residents in Rovato, near Brescia, Northern Italy.
(Photo: Luca Bruno, AP)The service is of great use in Lodetto, Martinelli’s hometown in the hard-hit Lombardy region of northern Italy.
“I won’t deny that having the chance to be out in the fresh air helps me relax,” Davide Martinelli said.